page.title: 13SENELEY GREEN CARNIVAL
page.content: The Seneley Green carnival is held every year on the 29th. of June. The organiser of the carnival is called Dot Carrington. She says where the stalls are to be positioned and everything. There are about twenty stalls in all and they are mostly refreshment stalls or they have games on them. The games include Mop the Bucket, Roll the Car and Throw the Dart. This is the third carnival there has been.Before the carnival there is a parade, in it is Garswood school, Play school, Guides, Scouts, Cubs and Brownies. There are three bands in it. The carnival begins at 2.00p.m. and lasts about 4 hours. Each organisation raises about Â£20 to Â£50 each. This year there is a Tug of War, Baby competition and a Break Dance competition.Also this year some Morris Men are coming.
